From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 01:20:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] misc: keep Fruit Jam usbhost PIO configured across reset

The wili8jam/Pico-PIO-USB host keeps its PIO USB engine configured while it
asserts and releases the root-port reset. The Linux bridge was reloading the
PIO state machines immediately after releasing SE0, which can disturb the
first post-reset full-speed idle/SOF window seen by the CH334F hub.

Configure the PIO engine before reset if needed, then leave it intact across
reset release and resume recovery SOFs/keepalives through that same engine.
Apply the same behavior to the HCD root-port reset helper and the manual
active probes so both paths exercise the same wili8jam-style timing.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -4483,9 +4483,6 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_reset_active(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh)
 	fj_usbhost_bus_reset_override(uh, false);
 	usleep_range(100, 200);
 
-	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_configure_sms(uh);
-	if (ret)
-		return ret;
 	uh->last_reset_ms = FJ_USBHOST_ACTIVE_RESET_MS;
 	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_sof_burst(uh, FJ_USBHOST_RESET_RECOVERY_FRAMES);
 	if (ret)
@@ -4596,11 +4592,14 @@ static void fj_usbhost_reset_bus(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh, u32 reset_ms)
 	if (use_pio) {
 		fj_usbhost_bus_reset_override(uh, true);
 		msleep(reset_ms);
 		fj_usbhost_bus_reset_override(uh, false);
 		usleep_range(100, 200);
-		if (fj_usbhost_pio_configure_sms(uh))
+		if (uh->pio_configured)
+			fj_usbhost_pio_sof_burst(
+				uh, FJ_USBHOST_RESET_RECOVERY_FRAMES);
+		else if (fj_usbhost_pio_configure_sms(uh))
 			msleep(FJ_USBHOST_POST_RESET_MS);
 		else
 			fj_usbhost_pio_sof_burst(
 				uh, FJ_USBHOST_RESET_RECOVERY_FRAMES);
 	} else {
